Now I see the issue. The type section is loaded as a vector of subtypes. Each subtype is loaded using `loadType(AST::SubType)`. Looking at `loadType(AST::SubType &)` at line 305:

```cpp
Expect<void> Loader::loadType(AST::SubType &SType) {
  EXPECTED_TRY(uint8_t B, FMgr.peekByte()...);
  switch (static_cast<TypeCode>(B)) {
  default:
    // Case: comptype.
    SType.setFinal(true);
    return loadCompositeType(SType.getCompositeType());
  case TypeCode::Sub:
    ...
  case TypeCode::SubFinal:
    ...
  }
}
```

So when the first byte of a subtype is `0x5f` (struct), it falls through to the default case which is `loadCompositeType`. That should work.

But now the type section content is loaded as a vector of subtypes with `VecCnt` entries. In my binary, the type section content is `02 5f 00 60 00 00`. Let me check what `loadVecCnt` returns. It reads a LEB128 value. `0x02` = 2, so VecCnt = 2.

Then for each of the 2 entries:
1. Peek byte: `0x5f` = TypeCode::Struct → default case → `loadCompositeType` (struct with 0 fields)
2. Peek byte: `0x60` = TypeCode::Func → default case → `loadCompositeType` (func type []→[])

This should work. Let me look at the error more carefully. The error says "section size mismatch, Code: 0x106". Maybe the issue is in `loadSectionContent`. Let me look at that:

