Still type section size mismatch. Let me compare with the working binary more carefully. In the working NullRefTestWasm, the type section starts at offset 8 and has 10 bytes. Content is `03 5f 00 60 01 7f 00 60 00 00`.

Since `loadVecCnt()` reads 4 bytes, at offset 10 (after section ID and size header), the bytes `03 5f 00 60` = 0x60005f03.

But the content only has 10 bytes total... So maybe `loadVecCnt()` in the type section doesn't use 4-byte uint32?

Wait, let me re-examine. Looking at the loader code again:

```cpp
Expect<void> Loader::loadSection(AST::TypeSection &Sec) {
  return loadSectionContent(Sec, [this, &Sec]() -> Expect<void> {
    // ...
    EXPECTED_TRY(uint32_t VecCnt, loadVecCnt().map_error(ReportError));
```

`loadVecCnt()` uses `FMgr.readU32()` which reads 4 bytes. But the section content for NullRefTestWasm is only 10 bytes. If we consumed 4 bytes for the count, there would only be 6 bytes left for 3 entries (struct, func, func). Each struct is minimum 2 bytes, each func is minimum 3 bytes = 2 + 3 + 3 = 8 > 6. That doesn't work.

Let me look at `FMgr.readU32()` more carefully. Maybe it reads LEB128:

